{"title_page": "HDFC Bank", "text_new": "'''https://www.indianewssamachar.com/'''\n\n\n\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} \n{{Infobox company\n| name = HDFC Bank Limited\n| logo = HDFC Bank Logo.svg\n| logo_size = 250px\n| type = [[Private company|Private]]\n| logo_caption = ''We understand your world''\n| area_served = [[India]]\n| key_people = {{ubl|[[Shyamala Gopinath]] <br>{{small|(Non-Exe Chairperson)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/board.asp?privcapId=101677|title=board of directors}}</ref>|[[Aditya Puri]]<br>{{small|([[managing director]])}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hdfcbank.com/assets/popuppages/senior_management.htm |title=HDFC Bank Senior Management |publisher=HDFC Bank Limited |date=8 November 2016 |accessdate=8 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/MrpezsTjoknJE8TneLLSjK/RBI-clears-reappointment-of-Aditya-Puri-as-HDFC-Bank-CEO-fo.html|title=RBI extended Mr.Puri's term|work=livemint|date=30 October 2018|accessdate=25 December 2018}}</ref>}}\n| industry = [[Banking]], [[financial services]]\n| products = [[Credit cards]], [[Retail banking|consumer banking]], [[Commercial bank|banking]], [[Financial services|finance and insurance]], [[investment banking]], [[mortgage loan]]s, [[private banking]], [[private equity]], [[wealth management]]<ref name=\"AR201213\">{{cite web|url = http://www.moneycontrol.com/financials/hdfcbank/balance-sheet/HDF01|title = Balance Sheet of HDFC Bank|publisher = moneycontrol}}</ref>\n| revenue = {{INRConvert|1166|b}} (2019)<ref name=\"HDFC Bank 2017\">{{cite web|url= https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/hdfc-bank-ltd/yearly/companyid-9195.cms|title=HDFC Bank 2017|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref>\n| operating_income = {{INRConvert|233|b}} (2019)<ref name=\"HDFC Bank 2017\"/>\n| net_income = {{INRConvert|211|b}} (2019)<ref name=\"HDFC Bank 2017\"/>\n| assets = {{INRConvert|11894|b}} (2019)<ref name=\"HDFC Bank\">{{cite web|url= https://www.hdfcbank.com/htdocs/common/pdf/corporate/Annual_Report_2016_17.pdf|title=HDFC Bank 2017|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref>\n| equity = \n| num_employees = 104,154 (June 30, 2019)<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.hdfcbank.com/htdocs/aboutus/News_Room/pdf/Press-release-Mar-19.pdf |title = FINANCIAL RESULTS (INDIAN GAAP) FOR THE QUARTER AND YEAR ENDED MARCH 31, 2019 |publisher = HDFC Bank Ltd}}</ref>\n| caption = \n| location = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| foundation = {{start date and age|df=y|August 1994}}\n| homepage = {{URL|www.hdfcbank.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''HDFC Bank Ltd.''' is an [[India]]n banking and financial services company headquartered in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]]. It has a base of 104154 permanent employees as of 30 June 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hdfcbank.com/|title=HDFC Bank|last=|first=|date=|website=HDFC Bank|publisher=HDFC Bank|access-date=}}</ref> HDFC Bank is [[India]]\u2019s largest private sector lender by assets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/zGj86RBk393NGlakNGPfAP/HDFC-Bank-most-valuable-brand-in-India.html|title=HDFC Bank most valuable brand in India: WPP study|last=|first=|date=September 10, 2015|website=Livemint|publisher=Livemint|access-date=}}</ref> It is the largest bank in [[India]] by market capitalisation as of March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/stocks/marketinfo/marketcap/bse/banks-private-sector.html|title=Largest bank by Market capitalization|last=|first=|date=|website=MoneyControl|publisher=MoneyControl|access-date=}}</ref> It was ranked 60th in 2019 BrandZ Top 100 Most Valuable Global Brands.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.millwardbrown.com/brandz/rankings-and-reports/top-global-brands/2019|title=Millward Brown - Top Global Brands 2019|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=hdfcbank.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nHDFC Bank was incorporated in 1994, with its registered office in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. Its first corporate office and a full service branch at Sandoz House, [[Worli]] were inaugurated by the then [[Ministry of Finance (India)|Union Finance Minister]], [[Manmohan Singh]].\n\nAs of June 30, 2019, the Bank's distribution network was at 5500 branches across 2,764 cities. The bank also installed 430,000 [[Payment terminal|POS]] terminals and issued 23570,000 debit cards and 12&nbsp;million credit cards in FY 2017.<ref name=\"HDFC Bank\"/>\n\n== Products and service ==\nHDFC Bank provides a number of products and services including [[wholesale banking]], [[retail banking]], treasury, auto loans, two wheeler loans, [[personal loan]]s, loans against property, consumer durable loan, lifestyle loan and [[credit card]]s. Along with this various digital products are Payzapp and SmartBUY.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://business.mapsofindia.com/banks-in-india/hdfc/|title=HDFC Bank \u2013 About Banking Services, Loans Scheme, Award, Contact Address, and more|website=business.mapsofindia.com|access-date=2016-07-16}}</ref>\n\n==Mergers==\nHDFC Bank merged with Times Bank in February 2000. This was the first merger of two private banks in the New Generation [[Private-sector banks in India|private sector banks]] category.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://profit.ndtv.com/stock/hdfc-bank-ltd_hdfcbank/reports|title=HDFC Bank: Reports, Company History, Directors Report, Chairman's Speech, Auditors Report of HDFC Bank - NDTVProfit.com|website=profit.ndtv.com|access-date=2016-07-16}}</ref> Times Bank was established by Bennett, Coleman and Co. Ltd., commonly known as [[The Times Group]], India\u2019s largest media conglomerate.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bandyopadhyay|first=Tamal|url=https://www.livemint.com/Industry/R9RVglpE4GP7OdDFN9wRPO/Bank-for-the-buck.html|title=A Bank for the Buck|date=19 November 2012|work=Live Mint|access-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Centurion Bank was acquired by HDFC Bank. HDFC Bank Board approved the acquisition of CBoP for 95.1&nbsp;billion [[Indian rupee|INR]] in one of the largest mergers in the financial sector in [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.banknetindia.com/banking/80142.htm|title=HDFC Bank to acquire Centurion Bank of Punjab|last=|first=|date=|website=Banknet India|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Investments ==\nIn March 2020, HDFC bank made investment of \u20b91,000 crores in Yes bank. As per the scheme of reconstruction of Yes Bank, 75% of the total investment by the Corporation would be locked in for 3 years. On March 14, Yes Bank allotted 100 crore shares of face value of \u20b92 each for a consideration of \u20b910 per share (including \u20b98 premium) to the Corporation aggregating to 7.97 per cent of the post issue equity share capital of Yes bank.\n\n==Listings and shareholding==\n\nThe [[equity shares]] of HDFC Bank are listed on the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] and the [[National Stock Exchange of India]]. Its American Depository Shares are listed on [[NYSE]] and the [[global depository receipt]] are listed on the [[Luxembourg Stock Exchange]] where two GDRs represent one equity share of HDFC Bank<ref name=\"Shareholding\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Shareholders (as of 31 December 2015) !! Shareholding<ref name=\"Shareholding\">{{cite web |url = http://www.moneycontrol.com/company-facts/hdfcbank/shareholding-pattern/HDF01|title = HDFC bank listing & shareholding|publisher = Money Control}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Corporate promoter|Promoter]] group ([[Housing Development Finance Corporation|HDFC]])||21.57%\n|-\n| Foreign [[institutional investor]]s (FII)||32.4%\n|-\n| Individual shareholders||8.5%\n|-\n| Bodies corporate||7.5%\n|-\n|[[Insurance]] companies||5.38%\n|-\n|[[Mutual fund]]s/[[Unit Trust of India|UTI]]||8.65%\n|-\n|[[Non-resident Indian and person of Indian origin|NRI]]/OCB/others||0.29%\n|-\n|[[Financial institution]]s/[[bank]]s||2.75%\n|-\n|[[American Depositary Share|ADS]]/[[Global depository receipt|GDR]]s||18.78%\n|}\n\n== Corporate social responsibility ==\nHDFC Bank's Parivartan initiative has spent \u20b94438&nbsp;million towards CSR in 2018-19<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://indiacsr.in/csr-space-is-still-in-a-fairly-nascent-stage-and-evolving-every-day-ashima-bhat-group-head-csr-hdfc-bank/ |title = CSR space is still in a fairly nascent stage and evolving every day: Ashima Bhat, Group Head \u2013 CSR, HDFC Bank \u2013 India CSR Network}}</ref> making it the third largest CSR spender in [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/hdfc-bank-hikes-csr-spend-by-47-in-2-years/articleshow/61789021.cms |title = HDFC Bank hikes CSR spend by 47% in 2 years - Times of India}}</ref>\n\n== Fraud ==\nOn Jan 29, 2020 Reserve Bank of India imposes monetary penalty on HDFC Bank Limited for failure to undertake on-going due diligence in case of 39 current accounts opened for bidding in initial public offer.\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rbi.org.in/Scripts/BS_PressReleaseDisplay.aspx?prid=49273|title=RBI imposes penalty on HDFC bank|website=rbi.org.in|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n\nThere are also known instances of users reporting signature forgery and replacement of application documents by HDFC employees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sandeephegde.com/blog/hdfc-bank-forged-my-signature-and-changed-application-form/|title=HDFC Bank forged my signature and changed application form|website=sandeephegde.com|date=19 November 2019|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref>\n\nA HDFC bank manager arrested for Rs 59.41 lakh fraud in Odisha<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/sep/16/former-hdfc-bank-manager-arrested-for-rs-5941-lakh-fraud-in-odisha-2034332.html|title=A HDFC bank manager arrested for Rs 59.41 lakh fraud in Odisha|website=newindianexpress.com|access-date=2019-08-16}}</ref>\n\nAltico Capital and Dubai's Mashreq Bank have approached the Reserve Bank of India, accusing HDFC BankNSE -1.82% of violating regulatory provisions by debiting part of the funds the company had raised through external commercial borrowing (ECB) and parked at the Indian bank. The local bank's decision to transfer money from account may be a violation of the RBI's end-use rule, they said.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/banking/altico-and-mashreq-approach-rbi-against-hdfc-bank/articleshow/71546523.cms|title=Altico and Mashreq approach RBI against HDFC Bank|website=economictimes.indiatimes.com|access-date=2019-10-13}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and recognition==\n===2019===\n*Best Bank: New Private Sector - FE Best Bank awards [https://www.hdfcbank.com/content/api/contentstream-id/723fb80a-2dde-42a3-9793-7ae1be57c87f/7a11082e-9cf6-4c4f-9de3-7e9ff409ba76?]\n*Winner in Innovation and Inclusiveness in Priority Sector Lending - 11tg Inclusive Finance India Awards (IFI) 2019 [https://www.hdfcbank.com/content/api/contentstream-id/723fb80a-2dde-42a3-9793-7ae1be57c87f/97fcd69c-ffa7-4bac-ab8f-d123ad88d8aa?]\n*Ranked 1st in 2019 BrandZ Top 75 Most Valuable Indian Brands HDFC Bank was featured for the 6th consecutive year.[https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/money-and-banking/hdfc-bank-retains-ranking-as-indias-valuable-brand/article29533162.ece/amp/]\n*''Among The Most Honored Company List,'' [https://www.hdfcbank.com/htdocs/aboutus/awards/pdf/Institutional-Investor-August-2019.pdf Institutional Investor All-Asia (ex-Japan) Executive Team 2019 survey]\n*[https://www.hdfcbank.com/htdocs/aboutus/awards/pdf/Indias-Best-Bank-June-11-2019.pdf ''India\u2019s Best Bank,'' Euromoney Awards for Excellence 2019]\n*''Bank of the Year and Best Large Bank,'' Business Today \u2013 Money Today Financial Awards 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hdfcbank.com/htdocs/aboutus/awards/pdf/Business-Today-Best-Bank-Awards-March-2019.pdf|title=Business Today \u2013 Money Today Financial Awards 2019|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*''Best Bank in India 2019'', by Global magazine FinanceAsia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zeebiz.com/companies/news-hdfc-bank-bags-the-best-bank-in-india-title-by-financeasia-magazine-expect-this-big-measures-in-2019-from-the-lender-103730|title=HDFC Bank bags the 'Best Bank in India' title by FinanceAsia magazine - expect this big measures in 2019 from the lender|date=2019-06-28|website=Zee Business|language=en|access-date=2019-06-28}}</ref>\n*''Ranked 60th in 2019 BrandZ Top 100 Most Valuable Global Brands''<ref name=\":0\" /> HDFC Bank was featured BrandZ Top 100 Most Valuable Global Brands 2019 for the 5th consecutive year. The Bank's brand value has gone up from $20.87&nbsp;billion in 2018 to $22.70&nbsp;billion in 2019.\n*''Best Large Bank'' & ''Fastest Growing Large Bank in 2019,'' by Business World Magna Awards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hdfcbank.com/htdocs/aboutus/awards/pdf/Businessworld_Best_Bank_Awards_May_15_2019.pdf|title=Business world Magna Awards|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===2016===\n*''Best Banking Performer, India'' in 2016 by Global Brands Magazine Award.<ref name=\"gbm-2016\">[http://www.globalbrandsmagazine.com/award-winners-2016/ Global Brands Magazine Award 2016 winners]</ref>\n*Best Performing Branch in [[Microfinance]] among private sector banks by NABARD, 2016, Award for Best Performance in Microfinance<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/HDFC-Bank-wins-microfinance-award-from-NABARD-in-Goa/articleshow/50689010.cms|title=HDFC Bank wins microfinance award from NABARD in Goa|last=|first=|date=January 22, 2016|website=Times of India|publisher=|language=en-US|access-date=2016-03-01}}</ref>\n*[[KPMG]] study of India's Best Banks, Bank of the year & best digital banking initiative award 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businesstoday.in/best-banks/2015/|title=Bank of the Year/ Digital Bank: HDFC BANK|last=|first=|date=|website=Business Today|publisher=|access-date=2016-03